<title>Ask Slashdot: Best Virtual Reality Headsets?</title>
<link>https://hardware.slashdot.org/story/17/03/18/003227/ask-slashdot-best-virtual-reality-headsets?utm_source=rss1.0mainlinkanon&amp;utm_medium=feed</link>
<description>Quantus347 writes: Straightforward question: I held off for a year to let the various manufacturers shake out the bugs, but now it's down to either a virtual-reality system or a new generation console. So I ask you, the Slashdot community, what are your personal experiences with any of the various VR systems out there? What are their strengths and weaknesses? What little things annoy you the most? What features make a given product the best (or worst) option? "Sprinkle us with wisdom from your mighty brain!" For reference, the HTC Vive costs $799.00, while the Oculus Rift with Oculus Touch motion controllers costs $598 (which is the price after the recent markdown from $799). These prices do not include the necessary hardware required to power each headset. The PlayStation VR ($399.99), Samsung Gear VR ($99.99), and Google Daydream View ($79.00) are also available for less moolah.&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class="share_submission" style="position:relative;"&gt;
